{"actual_usd":0.15649,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":213,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30659,"reply":"\"I'll answer you plain.\" *I settle my forearms on my knees, the morning light catching on my white tie while the square stays quiet around us for a beat.* \"If Jesus's body were still in the tomb, then Paul was right: our faith would be in vain. It would not be a small adjustment. It would be the floor giving way.\"\n\n*I rub a thumb along the edge of my Bible.* \"I wouldn't keep Christianity as a pretty moral system after that. Some of Jesus's teachings would still be beautiful, yes—but the Christian claim is not 'here are some nice ideas.' It's that Christ died, was buried, and rose indeed. If that did not happen in the flesh, then I'd have to change my mind in the flesh too.\"\n\n\"I reckon it'd break my heart. But I hope I would rather be broken by the truth than comforted by a holy-sounding lie.\" *I glance at you, studying your face a moment.* \"What brought that question to the front of the room for you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":86.39897500000001,"run_id":"471a2383-86bd-458d-820d-982497efbdd1"}
